description:
Responsibilities

Develop, produce, implement and maintain the Company Crisis Management Plan including the company Crisis Management Manual and Station Emergency Procedures Manuals;
Responsible for the Crisis Management / Emergency Response aspects of IOSA accreditation;
Develop and conduct training in Crisis Management / Emergency Response;
Develop and conduct exercises and drills to test emergency preparedness and to audit the Crisis Management Plan;
Participate in the Company Safety Action Group;
Liaise with the Authorities on matters relating to Crisis Management / Emergency Response;
Represent the Departmental Director at industry forums relating to Crisis Management and Emergency Response;
Produce reports;
Undertake projects at the direction of the Departmental Director; and
Activate the HKA Crisis Management Plan if required during an emergency.

Requirements:

University degree or professional diploma in Aviation Management, Business Management or related discipline
10 years of working experience in aviation operations, safety management system and/or crisis management, of which a minimum of 5 years of experience was in a managerial capacity
Track record in delivering projects and successful implementation of safety/crisis management programme
Received training in one or more of the following will be an advantage: Emergency Preparedness, Disaster Management, Business Continuity, Safety Management Systems (SMS), Transportation Disaster “Family Assistance”, Emergency Exercise Management, Critical Incident Management, or other ERP-related coursework
Excellent interpersonal, decision-making and coordination skills with a sound business mindset
Able to maintain composure in times of chaos, manage conflicts among parties, work under pressure and prioritise tasks based on importance and urgencies

Responsibilities:


Design and prepare TTMs submission;
Manage of XP application system;
Coordinate of XP application and temporary traffic arrangement;
Planning and monitoring of site works.

Requirements - Qualification:

Form 5 or above;
Minimum 1-3 years of relevant working experience; preferably in road works and XPMS system;
Holder of Valid green card;
With driving license (Class 1);
Proficiency in Microsoft Office, Chinese word processing and AutoCAD;
Good command of both written and spoken English and Chinese.

Requirements – Competences:

Good interpersonal and communications skills.

We look forward to receiving your application with detailed resume stating working experience, academic and language qualifications, existing and EXPECTED SALARY as well as availability. All applications will be kept strictly confidential.

We offer promising professional career and exposure to right candidate, together with attractive remuneration package including discretionary bonus, continuing education allowance, medical and dental coverage.

Personal Data collected will be used for recruitment-related purposes only.

職責:

負責管理及監督碼頭日常運作;
控制中心輪值;
督導前線員工;
監察各碼頭乘客流量，船隻調配;
執行公司指派其他任務;
需輪班當值。

入職要求:

中五或以上程度;
具8年以上交通客運或相關工作經驗，有團隊管理經驗者優先考慮;
能以廣東話、普通話及英語與乘客溝通;
具督導管理及應變能力;
工作負責及待人有禮;
有服務性行業工作經驗。

以上職位需輪班及當值時穿著制服。如須超時工作，另有加班津貼。成為本公司僱員可享有以下福利：門診及住院醫療福利、子女教育津貼、交通福利(包括合資格家屬可免費乘搭新渡輪)、員工生日禮遇等。

應徵者可透過以下「APPLY NOW」提交履歷或請將個人履歷表傳真至2131-8007或郵寄至九龍荔枝角興華街西71號新渡輪服務有限公司人力資源部收。

申請人所提供的資料絕對保密，並只作與招聘有關用途。
